# GitHub Pages Constraints & Deployment

This site is hosted on **GitHub Pages** at the custom domain **maximized.site**.

## Static only
- Static files ONLY. No server-side rendering, no PHP, no Node.js runtime.
- No API routes, no databases. Forms use Formspree (third-party) or `mailto:`.

## Links & paths
- Internal links use relative paths (`./about.html`) or root-relative paths
  consistent with serving from the root domain.
- All assets live under `/assets/` with subfolders:
  `/assets/css/`, `/assets/js/`, `/assets/images/`, `/assets/fonts/`.
- Images must be committed under `/assets/images/` or served from an approved CDN.

## CNAME
- The `CNAME` file (contains `maximized.site`) MUST NEVER be deleted or modified.

## 404
- `404.html` MUST live at the repo root for GitHub Pages custom 404 support.

## Storage
- Do NOT use `localStorage` or `sessionStorage` (may be blocked in embedded
  contexts). Use in-memory state instead.

## Deployment
- The GitHub Actions workflow at `.github/workflows/pages.yml` deploys from the
  `main` branch using `actions/upload-pages-artifact` + `actions/deploy-pages`.
- Required permissions: `contents: read`, `pages: write`, `id-token: write`.

## Build tooling
- No build step is required. If a `package.json` / `Makefile` is added for dev
  tooling (e.g. `live-server`), it MUST be documented in `README.md` and MUST
  NOT be required to serve the site.
